data.description: Great West Salem location, at the end of a cul-de-sac with RV parking. Laminate floor and wainscotting in family room and kitchen. Gas range, reverse osmosis system. Gas heat and A/C. Gas stove in family room. Spacious private backyard with covered patio, BBQ area with gas outlet. 2 storage sheds, sprinkler system. New dishwasher & microwave.
data.whatILove: We have loved living in this house because it is very quiet and private. The neighborhood is friendly and has very little traffic!  The house is so well insulated you can't hear anything outside, even heavy rain! The covered patio is nice year-round especially being able to BBQ any time of year! Overhead misting system at the covered patio for those hot summer days is refreshing. The landscaping is beautiful and colorful all year around.  During spring, summer and fall, the wisteria covered pergola at the master bedroom deck is a sight to see. The humming birds are abundant along with many other types of birds.  Make sure to taste the water from the 11-stage reverse osmosis water filter installed at the sink and refrigerator is the best water we have ever tasted!
